NBA DRAFT
June 28, 2007
Marco Belinelli
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
  Q.  You're going to Coach Don Nelson who has a good track record with foreign players.  Do you know anything about Coach Nelson, and are you excited to play for him?   
 MARCO BELINELLI:  Yeah, I know that Coach Nelson is a very great coach, so I'm so proud to play on his team.   
  
  Q.  How ready do you feel for the NBA game having played overseas already?   
 MARCO BELINELLI:  I think I'm ready, but I have to work to improve myself.   
 But I think that I'm okay for the NBA.  Only I have to work but I work, so it's okay.   
  
  Q.  Did you pattern your game against any NBA players?   
 MARCO BELINELLI:  Yeah, I played against LeBron James in the National Team in the World Championship.   
 This moment starts my life for the NBA.   
  
  Q.  Favorite player?   
 MARCO BELINELLI:  Kobe Bryant.   
  
  Q.  You'll actually be playing against Kobe a lot being on the same coast as him.  Are you excited or afraid to be up against your hero?   
 MARCO BELINELLI:  I'm very excited to play against him.  For the future maybe we'll play together -- he's a star for me, so, who knows.   
   
  End of FastScripts   

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT